  • All Classes Interface Summary Class Summary 
    Class Description
    CheckMonitor
    A singleton that monitors the state of closable and return values, to ensure that their values are checked.
    CheckMonitor.CheckableListener
    A listener into the closeable object to have it tell the monitor when various object lifecycle events take place.
    CheckMonitor.CloseableListener
    A listener into the closeable object to have it tell the monitor when various object lifecycle events take place.
    CloseableCollection
    A container for multiple AutoCloseable (and thus Closeable) objects.
    DebugCheckMonitor
    Maintains information about objects that need to be checked in a phantom reference cleaner.
    FileProblem
    A problem that comes from a known file.
    LocalizedProblem
    Problem with a simple, localized message text.
    MockCheckMonitor
    A mock check monitor, suitable for testing.
    MockCheckMonitor.RegisteredCheckable
    Checkable listener class that's suitable for testing.
    MockCheckMonitor.RegisteredCloseable
    Tracks the number of times the closeable is called.
    NonnullBiConsumer<T,​V>
    An equivalent to BiConsumer, where the parameters are non-null.
    NonnullConsumer<T>
    A version of Consumer but with an explicit nonnull value.
    NonnullFirstBiConsumer<T,​V>
    An equivalent to BiConsumer, where the first argument is non-null.
    NonnullFunction<T,​R>
    A version of Function that explicitly returns a non-null value, and takes a non-null parameter value.
    NonnullParamFunction<T,​R>
    A version of the Function interface where the parameter is explicitly non-null, and the return value is nullable.
    NonnullReturnFunction<T,​R>
    A version of the Function interface with an explicitly non-null return value, but nullable parameter value.
    NonnullSupplier<T>
    A version of the Supplier interface with an explicit non-null return value.
    NoOpCheckMonitor
    A monitor that performs no actual monitoring.
    Problem
    A standard problem that prevents a valid value from being returned.
    ProblemCollector
    Collects problems from multiple requests to gather data.
    ProblemContainer
    An object that contains problems.
    Ret
    Utility class for working with collections of return values.
    RetNullable<T>
    A problem container that contains a nullable value or problems, but not both.
    RetVal<T>
    A non-null value holder version of a problem container.
    RetVoid
    A simple returnable that can have problems, but no value.
    SourcedProblem
    A problem that includes a known source.
    UnhandledExceptionProblem
    A problem that comes from an exception that wasn't properly handled.
    ValueAccumulator<T>
    Allows for accumulating a list of values, some of which may have errors associated with them.
    ValueBuilder<T>
    Contains a non-null value and accumulates problems as aspects of the value are updated.
    WarningVal<T>
    A container for a non-null value and associated problems.
